===Conjunction===
{{en-con}}

# In order that
#: ''Eat your broccoli '''so''' you can have dessert.''
# With the result that, For this reason, [[therefore]]
#: ''I was hungry '''so''' I asked if there was more food.''
#: ''He ate too much cake, '''so''' he got sick.''
#: ''He wanted a book, '''so''' he went to the library.''

====Usage notes====
When used as the [[conjunction]] in a [[w:Conditional sentence|conditional sentence]], instead of the usual English word order in the [[apodosis]], [[w:wh-movement|wh-movement]] is used instead. Eg:
: ''If he can run a marathon, '''so''' <u>can you</u>.''
Chiefly in North American use, a [[coma]] or [[pause]] is often used before the conjunction when used in the second sense.

